post_text:
First and foremost, on behalf of our Staff, the Board of Education, and most of all our Students, we would like to send a huge THANK YOU out to the community for your support of the bond. Your vote will make a difference for generations to come.
Letters were mailed out yesterday to parents with further information about our return to school plan. We will offer to families both a face to face option as well as a remote learning option. Enclosed with the letter is the Family Education Option form and a self-addressed stamped envelope. Please make your selections on the form, and return it to us ASAP.
If you do not receive the letter by Tuesday, August 11th please call any of the three school offices, and we will be happy to assist you. Next week we plan to share out more details about our plan which will be finalized at Monday night's board meeting.
We appreciate everyone's patience as we prepare for students to return to school. Please visit our website at www.morleystanwood.org to view the letter.

July 6 at 8:36 AM ·

💛💙 Mohawk families, I need your help 💙💛

Vivianne from Germany 🇩🇪 has been planning on attending Morley Stanwood High School this year, but due to unforeseen circumstances, her host family can no longer host.

Vivianne turns 16 this month and enjoys theatre🎭, photography📷, drawing & bullet journaling. She has been learning to play the piano🎹. Vivianne describes herself as being funny, friendly, honest and reliable. Vivianne is allergic to cats and can’t live with them, however dogs are okay. She has a Boxer-Ridgeback mix named Sky.

Vivianne would love that her host family have children her age. She is also open to a double exchange student placement. Vivianne can share a bedroom with another female of approximate same age.

If you would like to know more about how to host Vivianne or find out about other students available to host, please contact Michelle Rogers with ICES, USA at 231-527-1224 or email at: mrogers@icesusa.org. ❤️ PLEASE SHARE ❤️

post_text:
On August 4, 2020, the Morley-Stanwood community will have the opportunity to vote on a school bond proposal for district-wide improvements and a two-year renewal of the existing school operating millage.

Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the Bureau of Elections will be mailing out absentee voter ballot applications to all registered voters for the August 4th election. If you’re interested in voting by mail, here’s what to do when you receive the application:

Step 1: Fill out the application for an absentee ballot according to the instructions and mail it in.

Step 2: When your ballot arrives, complete and return it. Ballots must be received by the County Clerk by August 4th at 8:00 PM.

Your polling location will also be open on August 4th for in-person voting from 7:00 AM to 8:00 PM.

Are you registered to vote? If not, visit https://mvic.sos.state.mi.us/

post_text:
Monday, June 1 Morley Stanwood Community Schools will be picking up all school devices (K-12) including the devices the district loaned out to students when school was closed for the remainder of the year. Buses will run their normal afternoon route, just like they had been doing for weeks delivering food. Please be ready around the same time to transfer your device back.

Included you should have the device itself, the case and the charger. Please double check to see that you have everything ready as this will save time on the route for folks further down the road.

At the same time school employees will be picking up devices, they will be returning any personal belongings that were left at school in lockers and desks.

Finally, if you wish, or if the above plan does not fit your schedule, the school will be open Monday, June 1 for you to drop off your child’s device at the school. The school will be open on the 1st from 10:30 AM to 5:30 PM for your convenience.

post_text: Tuesday, March 17th and Friday, March 20th MSCS will be delivering food to K-12 students by bus. We will run our regular end of the day bus routes, and deliver a three to four day supply of breakfast and lunches for students. We are attempting to make delivery times be around your regular drop off times. We are asking a parent or students to meet the bus to pick up the bags. Self transport students will be able to pick up meals at the high school on the south end between 3:00 and 3:30 on those same dates. We will load up the buses first, and then assist those who do not ride a bus, and are able to self pick up. A more detailed letter will be posted soon.

post_text: At this time, we would like to address some rumors that were brought to our attention as a result of social media posts. The district’s post relative to why the police were present at the school this morning stated, “there is no demonstrative threat to the school”. That simple post was blown up by careless individuals to include rumors of a mass shooting. We can tell you without a doubt that was never the case. Please, in the future pass on only the facts that are presented because to do otherwise is harmful and frightening to the children of the school and families of our community.

This letter is being shared with students at this time.
There is a rumor being spread by other students that something bad is going to happen here at school today, this is simply not true. post_text:
Community Members,

The following is a letter that was sent to staff later in the evening last night. We would like to share this information with you to let you know that we are doing everything we can to keep your children safe and you informed.
A high school student came to us after school claiming he'd heard a student on the bus saying he was bringing a gun to school tomorrow. The police were called and came to school to interview the student about what he says he heard. The police interviewed the other student and several potential witnesses. The police are convinced there was a miscommunication and NO threat was made. With that said, it is very likely to have the liaison officer, and possibly several other police cars at school tomorrow morning.MSCS takes these threats very seriously. We feel that at this time there is NOT an active threat against the school so please go about business as usual.

Attention Elementary Parents... if you are planning to enroll a new student in our building, we are asking that you come in as soon as possible. Please bring your child's original state- certified birth certificate, an official immunization record and parent proof of residence (electric bill, gas bill, residence tax bill)...we will make copies.

We'd like to get all incoming students registered by Friday, August 16th in order to get them started for the first day of school.

Please call our office with any questions at 231.856.7684 (7am-3pm Monday-Friday).

post_text:
Looking for Donations:

The Elementary Office is looking for donations of gently used sweatpants, underpants, t-shirts, tennis shoes. We use them for students who have accidents and/or need clothing at school.

Keep us in mind over the summer...if you clean out kids closets and dressers, rather than dropping them off elsewhere. We can always use them!

We also take donations of Snack-Size baggies in the office for making ice packs for student injuries.

We are in the office through June 21st and then back in the office August 1st to accept any donations... thank you in advance!

Morley Stanwood Bands
March 13, 2019 at 10:02 AM ·

On St. Patrick's Day, this Sunday, March 17, 2019 from 1-4 p.m., the Stanwood Eagles will be hosting an event to benefit the Morley Stanwood Bands.

The Eagles will be selling $5 reuben slider baskets with your choice of hot chips or sweet potato fries, featuring drink specials, and playing bar bingo.

In addition, there will be a silent auction and raffles to benefit the Morley Stanwood Bands program. (Gift baskets and gift cards for the silent auction are being collected at this time. If you or your business would like to make a donation, please contact Chrissy @ (231) 598-2138.)

Shamrocks will be sold at the Morley Stanwood Bands Concert on Thursday, March 14, 2019 at 7:00 p.m., and will also be available for purchase at the St. Patrick's Day event. Shamrocks are $1 each and all proceeds will be donated to the Band Boosters.

shared_text:
Morley Stanwood Bands
March 14, 2019 at 10:56 AM ·

Morley Stanwood Community, please join us tonight, Thursday, March 14, 2019 @ 7:00 p.m. for the All-District Band Concert!!

See the progression of our musicians' learning as you listen to the 6th, 7th, 8th, and H.S. Concert Bands in the MSHS Gymnasium.

The 7th, 8th, and High School Bands all recently performed for the MSBOA DIstrict 1 Concert Band Festival and earned ratings of 4, 3, and 1 respectively, with the HS band earning the right to compete at the State Festival in May. Hear them play some of their Festival performance music tonight!

Additionally, see/hear the newly created High School Choir Class perform!! There is no entrance fee, although the band WILL be accepting donations, as they continue to fundraise for new marching band uniforms.

Please join us to show community support for the work these kids do when they're not marching on the football field and wearing Hawaiian shirts in the gym bleachers at basketball games, as there's much more to it! 😉
We hope to see you there!
